    Links  � &amp; Resources     
   
   
         
    Ever growing �    
       
    Computer
  Professionals for Social Responsibility    
    http://www.cpsr.org/  
   Just as the name says. Lots of resources related to the
  general theme of the class. 
       
    American Civil
  Liberties Union    
    http://www.aclu.org/  
   Here you can find many legal actions involving computer
  technologies. 
       
    Edupage    
    http://www.educause.edu/pub/edupage/edupage.html  
     ACM Technews     
     http://www.acm.org/technews/current/homepage.html       
   Both of these provide great summaries and links to stories
  about the implications of computer technology. 
       
    The Washington Post    
    http://www.washingtonpost.com/  
    The New York Times    
      http://www.nytimes.com/    
    The Los Angeles
  Times    
      http://www.latimes.com    
   These standard US newspapers regularly have news
  on technology, e.g., voting issues, privacy and law, etc. 
   Some of the older (archived) articles are accessible using
  your UCI account and going through the library home page. 
       
    The Miami Herald    
    http://www.miami.com/mld/miamiherald/  
   Reported all the action during 2000 and 2002 election
  fiascos. Stay tuned. 
       
    The Guardian
  Unlimited    
    http://www.guardian.co.uk/  
    BBC News    
    http://news.bbc.co.uk/  
   These British news organizations provide a non US centric
  point of view on some of the same issues about technology and privacy. 
       
    Democracy Now    
    http://www.democracynow.org/  
   A very different perspective on many current events
  including horror stories of computing technology and privacy violations. 
       
       
       
   
   
       
       
   
        

     

     

 

